    • isValidValue

      private boolean isValidValue(String column, String value)
      Validates the value entered for a given column before updating the database. Ensures that the input type matches what is expected for that column. Expected types: - Name fields (cashierName, managerName): alphabetic characters and spaces only - Working Hours, Total Hours, Pay Rate: numeric (integer or decimal) - Pay Date: valid date in the format YYYY-MM-DD - isActive: boolean value TRUE or FALSE (case-insensitive)
      Parameters:
      column - The database column being updated
      value - The input value entered by the user
      Returns:
      true if the value matches the expected format for that column, false otherwise
